snippet.title: What is Pi? (π explained)
snippet.description:
What is pi? (π explained)
a brief explanation of the constant Pi

Pi=3.14159265...
C = circumference = perimeter 
D = diameter = line dividing circle in half
R = radius = half the diameter

circumference to diameter ratios
Circumference / Diameter = Pi
Diameter x Pi = Circumference
Circumference / Pi = Diameter


radians
180 / pi = 1 radian

area of a circle
pi x Radius x Radius = area
pi x (Radius)^2 = area
